{
  "texts": [
    "Among all these papers, the only ones which deal with viscosity solutions in spaces of probability measures over infinite dimensional state spaces seem to be [28] and [36], but the authors there do not provide any uniqueness results.",
    "This is indeed a very difficult problem even when H = R d.",
    "Our theoretical contributions.",
    "It is evident from the literature review that the study of optimal control problems for interacting particle systems governed by stochastic evolution equations in infinite-dimensional Hilbert spaces, i.e.",
    "(1.1)-(1.2), and their mean-field limits (including convergence and uniqueness of solutions of the limiting PDE) is an open area of research."
  ]
}